{"id": "EUVD-2025-15932", "enisaUuid": "16416aed-e2a9-36da-a061-ad1828cb6155", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niommu: Fix two issues in iommu_copy_struct_from_user()\n\nIn the review for iommu_copy_struct_to_user() helper, Matt pointed out that\na NULL pointer should be rejected prior to dereferencing it:\nhttps://lore.kernel.org/all/86881827-8E2D-461C-BDA3-FA8FD14C343C@nvidia.com\n\nAnd Alok pointed out a typo at the same time:\nhttps://lore.kernel.org/all/480536af-6830-43ce-a327-adbd13dc3f1d@oracle.com\n\nSince both issues were copied from iommu_copy_struct_from_user(), fix them\nfirst in the current header.", "datePublished": "2025-05-20T18:30:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T15:31:28", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37900", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2e303d010722787dc84d94f68d70fe10dfc1b9ea", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/30a3f2f3e4bd6335b727c83c08a982d969752bc1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/967d6f0d9a20a1bf15ee7ed881e2d4e532e22709"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37900", "GHSA-j23c-3429-q5qm"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "154ca92d-7d63-32dc-9077-ef0507b59c48", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.28"}, {"id": "1c9c6885-3737-3452-a5d9-d998c42f2e92", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.6"}, {"id": "2213824c-3294-388d-a184-8f3273b3c1ba", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "273dc7b7-3554-3b69-b5e9-05639ef3df5c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e9d36c07bb787840e4813fb09a929a17d522a69f <967d6f0d9a20a1bf15ee7ed881e2d4e532e22709"}, {"id": "3f1842c0-98b3-3180-bb18-f76a0d93a788", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e9d36c07bb787840e4813fb09a929a17d522a69f <2e303d010722787dc84d94f68d70fe10dfc1b9ea"}, {"id": "6f860302-53be-3680-8b50-82406699bec6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15"}, {"id": "c4